        "content": "<p>cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12897#discussion_r3011597764\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In order to avoid expensive ops that will be in the critical path of string-carrying APIs, could we use AND instead of an integer mod here (latter can be ~50 cycles or more)? Something like</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"fm\">debug_assert!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">align</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">is_power_of_two</span><span class=\"p\">());</span>\n<span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">align</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">!=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>",
